         <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve"><head>Translation</head>
            <div type="translation" source="#edd" xml:lang="en"><p>With good fortune. Under the most magnificent Paulos, consularis, this work took place.</p></div>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p>On the building see Kraeling, p.140f. </p>
            <p>Line 3, Paulus: PLRE III, Paulus 14; the phrasing suggests an official. The title suggests a date in the sixth century unless Paulus' 
                    appointment was extraordinary, see the discussion by Kraeling loc. cit. Kraeling assigns 
                    him responsibility for very considerable reorganisation of the building and notes that this would 
                    be surprising if he held office after the seat of government was moved from Ptolemais to Apollonia; 
                    it is probably better to suppose that his responsibility was limited to a "redecoration" which included 
                    laying the surviving pavement in which the inscription is embedded.</p>
         </div>
         
